              Introduction
                
                China Venture Capital Yearbook 2006, the 3rd 
                annual series work, is an authoritative  comprehensive reference 
                on venture capital in China, produced by a group of prominent 
                academic scholars, industry leaders and government officials headed 
                by Siwei Cheng, Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the 
                National People's Congress (NPC), the People's Republic of China. 
                It is one of the feature publications edited by CVCRI in cooperation 
                with Public Policy Research Institute of Hong Kong Polytechnic 
                University,Ministry of Science and Technology of China, Guangdong 
                Venture Capital Association and Shanghai Venture Capital Association.
              The Yearbook serves as the most valuable 
                guide in China and overseas for business practitioners, academic 
                researchers, and government officials with a focus on China's 
                venture capital markets to capture latest developments, track 
                and assess historical data, seek practical insights and ideas, 
                and to identify and build business connections in the venture 
                capital communities inside and outside China..
            
        
      
  


  
  




















